#: ../../changelog.rst:1346
msgid ""
"``invoke`` has been turned on its head, and is now the `runs_once` decorator"
" (living in :mod:`fabric.decorators`). When used to decorate a function, "
"that function will only execute one time during the lifetime of a ``fab`` "
"run. Thus, where you might have used ``invoke`` multiple times to ensure a "
"given command only runs once, you may now use `runs_once` to decorate the "
"function and then call it multiple times in a normal fashion."
